snippet.textDisplay:
Hello Pakistan,
Here is my short life story.
I used to play with my friend Aslam in my village. It was time before partition. When there was no boundary.

I still miss those days when we used to sit together and share love and friendship. He was my only friend. We used to meet in the evening and we talk about our lives and future.
The suddenly one day he left with his family and I just stood there with a heartache.
Oh my God. I still remember each moment and cry very often.
I want to meet my old friend and his family and want to eat lunch in the same plate.
I know that he also feels the same and want to see me.
Our grandchildren might not understand this pain. I want to tell them not to hate Pakistan. I want to say this to Pakistan - don't hate us. Because we used to be one family. And I feel the same even today.
I want to see my friend before I die.

This is not my words but lots of old people have died with a hard feeling like this. ,
